'''''Biomphalaria''''' is a [[genus]] of air-breathing [[freshwater snail]]s, [[aquatic animal|aquatic]] [[pulmonate]] [[gastropod]] [[mollusk]]s in the [[family]] Planorbidae, the [[sheep|ram]]'s horn [[snail]]s and their allies.

''Biomphalaria'' is the [[type genus]] of the tribe [[Biomphalariini]].

''Taphius'' is a synonym for ''Biomphalaria''.<ref>Bouchet P. & Rocroi J.-P. (2005) "Classification and Nomenclator of Gastropod Families". ''Malacologia'' '''47'''(1-2): 167-168.</ref>

The shell of this species, like all planorbids is sinistral in coiling, but is carried upside down and thus appears to be dextral.

[[File:Biomphalaria tenagophila shell.png|thumb|Apical, apertural and umbilical view of the shell of ''[[Biomphalaria tenagophila]]''. Scale bar is 3 mm.]]

